==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Imperfection
<hw>Im`per*fec"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>imperfectio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>imperfection</ets>. See
<er>Imperfect</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <def>The quality or condition
of being imperfect; lack of perfection; incompleteness; deficiency;
fault or blemish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Sent to my account⟦br⟧
With all my <qex>imperfections</qex> on my head.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Defect; deficiency; incompleteness; fault;
failing; weakness; frailty; foible; blemish; vice.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Imperfectness</ent>⟦br⟧
